Whether you‚Äôre hosting a wedding, corporate gathering, birthday party, or community event, Millers Jump Time Entertainment offers high-quality tent rentals to elevate your celebration in Orlando , Lake Nona , St. Cloud , and Kissimmee . Why Rent Tents for Your Event? Tents provide more than just shelter‚Äîthey create an inviting atmosphere and serve as the foundation of your event setup. With Millers Jump Time Entertainment, you get tents that are stylish, durable, and versatile. Rain or shine, our tents keep your guests protected while enhancing the overall experience. Tent Rental Options for Any Occasion We understand that every event is unique, which is why we offer a variety of tent styles and sizes to match your needs: Pole Tents: Perfect for large gatherings like weddings or corporate events, offering ample space and a classic look. Frame Tents: Ideal for smaller spaces and events requiring flexible layouts, as they don‚Äôt need center poles. High-Peak Tents: Elegant and sophisticated, these tents add a touch of luxury to weddings, galas, and upscale events. Pop-Up Tents: Easy to set up and perfect for casual gatherings, vendor booths, or small backyard parties. Clear Top Tents: Add a modern touch to your event with transparent ceilings that allow natural light to shine through. Our team will work with you to determine the best tent option for your venue, guest count, and event theme. Serving Orlando, Lake Nona, St. Cloud, and Kissimmee Millers Jump Time Entertainment proudly serves the central Florida area, delivering top-notch tent rentals for events of all sizes. Orlando Tent Rentals: Whether it‚Äôs a corporate event at a downtown venue or a private celebration in a local park, our tents provide comfort and style. Lake Nona Tent Rentals: Transform your outdoor space with our elegant tents, perfect for weddings, family reunions, and community gatherings. St. Cloud Tent Rentals: From backyard birthday parties to school functions, we offer a variety of tent options to fit any occasion. Kissimmee Tent Rentals: Enhance your next festival, fundraiser, or church event with durable and attractive tents. Why Choose Millers Jump Time Entertainment for Tent Rentals? Quality You Can Trust: All our tents are made from premium materials, ensuring durability and a polished appearance for your event. Professional Setup and Take-Down: Let our experienced team handle the logistics, from timely delivery to secure installation and hassle-free cleanup. Customizable Solutions: We offer additional rental options like tables, chairs, and lighting to create a fully functional event space. Affordable Pricing: Our competitive rates and customizable packages ensure you get the best value for your investment. Local Expertise: As a trusted provider in central Florida, we understand the unique needs of events in Orlando, Lake Nona, St. Cloud, and Kissimmee. Perfect for Every Event No matter the occasion, our tent rentals add comfort, style, and versatility to your celebration. Common events include: Weddings: Create a stunning outdoor venue with a tent that complements your theme and accommodates your guest list. Corporate Events: From team-building activities to formal dinners, our tents provide a professional yet comfortable environment. Festivals and Fairs: Offer shade and shelter for attendees, vendors, and performers. Community Events: Host fundraisers, school functions, and church gatherings in a covered, weather-resistant space. Private Parties: Make birthdays, anniversaries, and graduations unforgettable with a stylish tent setup. Tips for a Successful Tent Rental Experience Measure Your Space: Ensure the chosen tent fits your event venue and leaves room for tables, chairs, and other features. Consider the Weather: Choose tent accessories like sidewalls, fans, or heaters to keep guests comfortable in any weather. Add Decor: Enhance the ambiance with lighting, draping, or floral arrangements that match your event‚Äôs theme. Plan Ahead: Book early to secure your preferred tent style, especially during peak event seasons. Bundle Rentals: Save time and money by renting additional items like tables, chairs, and linens from the same provider. Make Your Event Unforgettable with Millers Jump Time Entertainment At Millers Jump Time Entertainment, we take pride in helping you create memorable events with our high-quality tent rentals . Below you will find answers to our most frequently asked questions. You can also contact us via our simple online form. Sussex St, Cambridge There's nothing better than actually chatting to somebody face-to-face. You can still visit us in our city centre showroom. We are open 6 days a week. If you are making a special visit then you can either us our Priority Booking System or contact us first. 01223 354 452 You can call and talk to our team during opening hours using the number below. Our team endeavour answer all calls so you can talk to a real person and they are always happy to help with advice and support. Please note that some of our team members work from home on some days so may not be able to immediately check a showroom enquiry themselves but they can contact our showroom team if required. Online Contact Form For enquiries that aren't answers by our website or FAQs below we would ask you fill out our Contact Form using the button below. This is the best way to get in contact out of our hours or if your call isn't urgent. Our team monitor incoming messages every day and will contact you to discuss if necessary. FAQs Payment What are you payment options? We accept all major credit cards include American Express. We also accept payments via Apple Pay and Google Pay. Do you offer Finance? We no longer off Finance. The market for musical instrument finance changed during COVID and now most offers are between 15% and 24% APR. We believe there are far better deals for our customers available in the consumer finance market. How does Rental work? Our rental scheme is one our most popular and accessible services. With hundreds of instruments renting, we maintain an entire fleet and provide them for you to get started or get back into music. Find our more on our dedicated Rental Scheme Page Returns How can I return an item? The first step is to get in touch with our customer service time who can advise on the best process for your particular item. What is your Returns policy? Because of the nature of the items we sell we have different policies to cover these different areas. Our guiding principle is that we won't you to be satisfied with your purchase, that's why if you're considering a larger item we would recommend you visit our showroom to select. You can find full details of our returns policy here What happens if a product develops a fault? Many of the products we sell are covered by a comprehensive manufacturer warranty or by our own warranty. In the first instance get in touch so we can determine the problem and discuss next steps. Delivery Can I collect my order? Yes, absolutely. However unless it is a smaller item most of our products are stored off site and so you should wait until you receive confirmation of collection before making a journey. I have a specific requirement for my delivery. How can I organise this? Just contact our team who will be happy to discuss the best option for you. Can you collect my old piano? We certainly can collect. The best service really depends on whether you're looking to sell, part-exchange , or donate your instrument to our Piano Equals scheme . Tuning and Service Do you tune in my area? Our piano tuning service is available across East Anglia. We have online booking software available 24/7 here If you are unsure then please contact us for more information. Do you buy secondhand instruments? In short, yes. We believe one of the best ways to make the music industry more sustainable is to encourage reuse of quality musical instruments. We buy, sell, part-exchange, and donate pianos. You can find out more and apply here . We can part-exchange String instruments. For all other instruments we would encourage you to find a suitable specialist who can help. Do you repair other instruments? Repairing instruments and extending their life is extremely important. The skills loss in the UK is huge and we believe in trying to increase the longevity of instruments where we can. We work with a number of specialists who can offer repairs on digital pianos, string instruments, and french policy. Contact us for more information. Sustainability What is your policy regarding Sustainability? Musical instruments have historically been very repairable and lasted decades, even centuries. Sadly in many areas we have seen this reversed with products not lasting as long as becoming less repairable. At Millers Music our impact on the environment is something we take very seriously. we work to minimise our impact and improve the lives of those in our communities. We have a number of schemes and initiatives we run in order to achieve this and there is more information on our progress on our Sustainability page . What is WEEE? WEEE or the Waste¬†Electrical and Electronic equipment recycling scheme to give it its full title is a specialist part of the waste and recycling industry. In the piano industry this can apply to digital pianos, keyboards, synths but can also to apply to products requiring a battery such as piano lamps. How does your instrument donation scheme work? We believe in tackling the issues with sustainability and the growing inequality in music provision. There are hundreds of thousands (if not millions) of quality instruments already in the UK. We want to put these to use by reusing them where possible and if not recycling them. You can find out more about our instrument donation schemes here https://millersmusic.co.uk/pages/piano-equals Delivery Can I collect my order? I have a specific requirement for my delivery.
